          <h3 class="font-semibold text-foreground mb-2">And the Rest...</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Additional information and details</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bio Section -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-secondary/30">
    <div class="site-container">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
          <div data-aos="fade-right">
            <Image 
              src={speakerImage} 
              alt="Guido Jansen speaking at a conference"
              class="rounded-2xl shadow-lg w-full"
              width={600}
              height={400}
            />
          </div>
          <div data-aos="fade-left">
            <Badge class="mb-4">About the Speaker</Badge>
            <h2 class="h2 mb-6">Guido Jansen</h2>
            <div class="prose prose-lg text-muted-foreground space-y-4">
              <p>
                Guido is a digital psychology and experimentation consultant who helps organizations optimize their digital customer experiences through data-driven insights and behavioral psychology.
              </p>
              <p>
                With over 15 years of experience in e-commerce optimization, conversion psychology, and A/B testing, Guido has worked with hundreds of companies ranging from startups to Fortune 500 enterprises.
              </p>
              <p>
                He's the founder of CRO.CAFE and has spoken at 100+ conferences worldwide, sharing actionable insights on digital optimization, customer psychology, and experimentation culture.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Am I the Right Fit Section -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="site-container">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center mb-12" data-aos="fade-up">
        <div class="w-16 h-16 mx-auto mb-6 rounded-2xl bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center">
          <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-primary" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h2 class="h2 mb-6">Am I the right fit?</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl" data-aos="fade-up">
        <div class="prose prose-lg text-muted-foreground space-y-6 text-center">
          <p>
            Before you reach out, please ensure you understand my speaking goals and the specific objectives for the session. What is your ultimate goal, and who is your target audience? What do you want them to be able to say after the session? Please let me be clear that this is not to be difficult; this is to ensure my session is not just for your audience and deliver the content in the most useful way.
          </p>
          <p>
            To make this easy for you, I've created an online form you can fill out to give me all the needed information. Please fill out the form at least 3 months before your event.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-8">
            <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSf7yj4sn0qxaSbvnuIflFbN9C3SyFoz4crYQaJkdry9s8zWEg/viewform?usp=sf_link" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary">
              Contact Information Form
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Talk Format Section -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-secondary/30">
    <div class="site-container">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center mb-12" data-aos="fade-up">
        <div class="w-16 h-16 mx-auto mb-6 rounded-2xl bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center">
          <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-primary" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M7 4V2a1 1 0 011-1h8a1 1 0 011 1v2m0 0V3a1 1 0 011 1v1M7 4V3a1 1 0 011-1m0 0h8m-8 0V2m8 2v1m0-1V2m0 2h1M8 7h8v10H8V7z"></path>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h2 class="h2 mb-6">Talk format</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl" data-aos="fade-up">
        <div class="prose prose-lg text-muted-foreground space-y-6">
          <p>
            My talks are easy to understand sessions on usability, persuasion, conversion optimization, building experimentation culture, CRO teams and community building. They are usually designed for a wide variety of audiences and can be adapted to fit beginners as well as intermediate audiences. The focus is on building audience awareness while providing actionable takeaways.
          </p>
          <p>
            I usually prefer to present the opening or closing keynote at events, as it allows for more inspiration and practical insights. I'm experienced with live interviews or panels on-stage and will often engage with the audience for light content but will have conversations for the rest of the keynote. I'm also happy to organize the line-up where the technology-focused talks and insights follow, and I will focus on the background of your audience.
          </p>
          <p>
            Depending on the topic and the conference, I usually prefer to present the opening or closing keynote at events, with panels in-between technical talks. My talk usually lasts 30-60 minutes and suits an audience between 25-2500 people.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Fee Section -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="site-container">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center mb-12" data-aos="fade-up">
        <div class="w-16 h-16 mx-auto mb-6 rounded-2xl bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center">
          <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-primary" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8c-1.657 0-3 .895-3 2s1.343 2 3 2 3 .895 3 2-1.343 2-3 2m0-8c1.11 0 2.08.402 2.599 1M12 8V7m0 1v8m0 0v1m0-1c-1.11 0-2.08-.402-2.599-1"></path>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h2 class="h2 mb-6">Fee</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl" data-aos="fade-up">
        <div class="bg-card rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-sm border">
          <div class="text-center mb-8">
            <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-primary mb-2">€5000</div>
            <div class="text-lg text-muted-foreground">+ VAT + expenses (Travel + accommodation)</div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="prose prose-lg text-muted-foreground space-y-6">
            <p>
              My talks are about entertaining and teaching an audience. I do not sell any products or services in your presentations and I cannot afford to speak for free as a commercial conference – thanks for your understanding.
            </p>
            <p>
              This talk content and teaching your audience building, CRO teams and community building. They are usually designed for a wide variety of audiences, from building awareness, increasing and building communities and digital consultants. The focus is to increase knowledge while providing actionable takeaways that will support your audience and your event.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Payment Terms Section -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-secondary/30">
    <div class="site-container">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center mb-12" data-aos="fade-up">
        <h2 class="h2 mb-6">Payment terms</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl" data-aos="fade-up">
        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div class="prose prose-lg text-muted-foreground space-y-6">
            <p>
              At least €2500 should be paid in EUR (€) via wire transfer or PayPal to account. I pay my own taxes and fees in my country so this fee is net amount that I need to receive to speak for free at a commercial conference and events.
            </p>
            <p>
              My payment must be received before I speak for your event. Please let me know the form of payment you would be happy to provide, with my pay split being 3+ months before the session.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
            <div class="bg-card rounded-xl p-6 border">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-foreground">Deposit</h3>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground">50% of the quoted project fee to date as we move forward to speak the dates for your session.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-card rounded-xl p-6 border">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-foreground">Final Payment</h3>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground">The remaining balance due after your session is completed.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-card rounded-xl p-6 border">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-foreground">Booking Terms</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-muted-foreground">
              <li>• This is a no-strings-attached booking fee. When I receive it, you can count on the booked for your events.</li>
              <li>• Your payments cannot be refunded before I leave for your organization's signature on event.</li>
              <li>• The payment period and fee structure is <strong>non-negotiable</strong> for any given below, so you really have to negotiate higher fees if you need me to speak for any cheaper.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Testimonials Section -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="site-container">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center mb-12" data-aos="fade-up">
